<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Warns Against `Hasty' Decisions on Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Warns Against `Hasty' Decisions on Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505182294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1648 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Duma (the lower house of Russian 
parliament) has called both on Kiev and Simferopol for "a show 
of restraint and wisdom and renunciation of hasty or emotional 
actions". "We are aware of how hopeless and fatal can be any 
attempt to try to resolve by force controversial issues relating 
to a popular drive for self- determination", its appeal adopted 
late on Wednesday says. This was approved without discussion on 
Speaker of Parliament Ivan Rybkin's proposal. 
  The Duma speaks of "perceiving with hope a report on the 
first moves" for dialogue and consensus that Ukrainian and 
Crimean deputies made during talks in Kiev. 
  The Russian deputies expect their counterparts on both sides 
not to allow irresponsible politicians to endanger public peace 
and security because of their one-off considerations. 
  For its part, the Duma is prepared "with the delicate 
situation being taken into account" to do all it can to help 
towards the searches of compromise on the basis of the 
Russian-Ukrainian treaty of November 19, 1990. 
  "For the past two centuries, Crimea has served and we are 
sure, will continue to serve the interests of the fraternal 
nations of Ukraine and Russia", the appeal says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

