<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Accord Signed 25 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Accord Signed 25 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505171794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1636 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 25 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin and Acting Ukrainian Prime Minister Yefim 
Zvyagilsky, heads of the Russian and Ukrainian official 
delegations to the talks on the disputed Black Sea Fleet, will 
not sign an agreement on the division of the fleet today, a 
Russian Government official said. 
  The official said that the working groups will continue 
discussion for another 30 minutes and may adopt a joint 
communique. 
  Both delegations have contacted their presidents via the hot 
line several times and Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin met with his Ukrainian counterpart Yefim Zvyagilsky 
to discuss the issue. 
  The Ukrainian delegation agreed on Wednesday to return to 
one 
of the four variants of fleet division proposed by Russia and 
rejected by Ukraine earlier. 
  The stumbling block at the talks which have been underway 
for 
three days is the disagreement over the location of the 
Ukrainian and Russian navies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

