<H3> <TI>   Radiation at Ignalina Plant Said Within `Normal Limits' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radiation at Ignalina Plant Said Within `Normal Limits' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2505131394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2505131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Official statement"] </F>
  [Text] On 24 May, according to the schedule of the 
Civilian Defense of Minsk Oblast, a planned quarterly exercise 
was held to observe laboratory control networks, as well as to 
practice a complex of radiation protection measures in Myadel 
Rayon of Minsk Oblast. According to (?information) received 
from the State Hydrometeorological Committee [Halowhydromet], 
the State Committee for Nuclear Control [Dzyarzhatamnahlyad], 
and the management of the Ignalina Nuclear Power Plant, at 1200 
[0900 GMT] on 25 May, the radiation level around the Ignalina 
Nuclear Power Plant was within the normal limits. At the 
station itself, beginning in April, one energy unit has been 
under a scheduled repair. Operation of the second energy unit 
was halted for economic reasons, and it does not produce 
electric energy. 

</TEXT>

