<H3> <TI>   Statement on Civil Defense Exercise, Radiation Levels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement on Civil Defense Exercise, Radiation Levels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505164994 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Official report: On 24 May, according to the Minsk 
Oblast civil defense procedures plan, planned quarterly training 
was held for the networks of supervision and laboratory 
monitoring. Elaborate radiation protection measures were put 
into operation in Myadelskiy Rayon, Minsk Oblast. According to 
evidence obtained from the Main Hydrometeorology Service, the 
State Atomic Supervision and the leadership of the Ignalina 
nuclear power station, at 1200 today the radiation situation 
around the Ignalina nuclear power station was within normal 
limits. 
  Since April, one generating unit at the station itself has 
been undergoing a scheduled overhaul. The second generating 
unit has been halted for economic reasons and is not producing 
electricity. 

</TEXT>

