<H3> <TI>   New PTCDM Party Attacks `Incompetent' Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New PTCDM Party Attacks `Incompetent' Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505133694 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1300 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2505133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 25/5/1994 -- Ion Batcu, 
chairman of the Coordinating Council of the recently registered 
Peasant Christian Democratic Party of Moldova [PTCDM], declared 
today to BASAPRESS that "the current government is the most 
incompetent Moldova has ever had, being incapable of pulling the 
country out of its deep crisis." He specified that the PTCDM 
will lead the political movement of the peasant parties in 
Bessarabia. "We think the problems of the village are to be 
solved first. If the government does not do this, the crisis 
will never be overcome," said Batcu, mentioning that his party 
will be in opposition to the current governing forces. Tomorrow 
at noon, the PTCDM will hold a press conference, in the hall of 
the Journalists' Union (House of the Press). 

</TEXT>

