<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Reorganizes Control Department </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Reorganizes Control Department </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505125794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1047 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
transformed the control department of the president's 
administration into a control department of the Russian 
president. 
  The president's press service announced that this had been 
done in order to strengthen the control functions exercised by 
the president in Russia and to ensure efficiency and 
coordination of such activities. 
  In accordance with the provision on the control department, 
its main purpose is to exercise presidential control over 
implementation of the laws and presidential decrees and 
ordinances by the state federal bodies and bodies of the 
federation's constituent members on behalf of the president. 
  The department will also exercise control over: 
implementation of presidential decrees by the executive bodies 
and officials; over the activities of the executive bodies, 
enterprises, establishments and organizations on implementation 
of social and economic policy; and over activities of Russian 
diplomatic missions, trade offices and other establishments 
abroad. 
  The department will carry out examinations and consider 
appeals submitted to it by individuals, enterprises and 
organizations. 
  The Control Department has the right to demand from the 
federal executive bodies, enterprises, establishments and 
organizations, regardless of the form of property, all 
information required for its examinations . 
  If a violation is revealed during an investigation the 
department can submit its recommendations to the heads of the 
executive bodies for consideration within ten days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-63904 </DOCNO>
