<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Deputies Quit Liberal Democratic Union </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Deputies Quit Liberal Democratic Union </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505191894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1648 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Six State Duma deputies gave official notice 
Wednesday that they were leaving the Liberal Democratic Union of 
December 12. This decision was taken by five former members of 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's Liberal Democratic Party -- Viktor 
Kobelev, Aleksandr Pronin, Vladimir Novikov, Vladimir Borzyuk 
and Tatyana Bulgakova as well as Deputy Andrey Volkov. 
  Aleksandr Pronin told INTERFAX they had decided to leave 
because of disagreements with the line taken by the Union's 
leader Boris Fedorov and also the desire not to be in the same 
group as Andrey Makarov. 
  Another serious reason for the exit of the six was the fact 
that the leadership of the "Decembrists" had kept secret from 
ordinary members the fact that the leadership had met recently 
with President Boris Yeltsin and were therefore representing 
no-one but themselves. 
  "If Zhirinovskiy is openly practicing deceit, then the 
leaders of the Decembrists are doing it behind people's backs," 
said Pronin. 
  He said that the six deputies would not join any other 
factions but rather form an autonomous deputy group. 

</TEXT>

