<H3> <TI>   TV, Radio League Set Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TV, Radio League Set Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505213394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1437 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 25 May -- A decision to set up a Television 
and Radio League [Liga televideniya I radio] was taken today by 
representatives of over 100 all-Russian and regional state and 
independent radio and TV companies. Anatoliy Lysenko, general 
director of the All-Russia Radio and TV Company, was elected 
chairman of the body while it is being established. 
  The league will be a body of the Union of Journalists of 
Russia. In an interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent, Union 
Chairman Vsevolod Bogdanov voiced the hope that the league will 
be able to exert considerable influence on the framing of 
legislation in the TV and radio broadcasting field, will become 
a collective body defending the interests of the "electronic" 
press, and will enable a number of topical professional issues 
to be resolved. At the first organizational meeting, Grigoriy 
Shevelev, Ostankino's first deputy chairman, was instructed to 
take charge of the work of setting up an academy of radio and 
television. Other areas of the league's activities were also 
outlined. 

</TEXT>

