<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Explains Thinking Behind New Economic Package </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Explains Thinking Behind New Economic Package </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2505180194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 26 May 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2505180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Undated announcement by Russian president's press secretary </F>
Vyacheslav Kostikov: "In the Spirit of Civil Accord"] 
  [Text] In connection with the signing of a package of 
economic edicts encouraging activity by the government and 
legislative organs in the sphere of increasing the pace of 
economic reform, Russian President B.N. Yeltsin has sent letters 
to State Duma and Federation Council deputies explaining the 
motives behind the presidential initiative in the economic 
sphere. 
  The president points out to the deputies that his actions 
arise both out of actual constitutional prerogatives and out of 
the Treaty on Social Accord. In his letter B.N. Yeltsin informs 
the deputies that, acting in the spirit of civil accord, 
immediately after signing the package of economic edicts he 
instructed the government to submit draft laws based on the 
edicts to the deputies for their consideration. So the edicts, 
insofar as they impinge on the jurisdiction of the Federal 
Assembly, will remain valid until the relevant federal laws are 
adopted. 
  Moreover, on 24 May the president proposed that V.S. 
Chernomyrdin, I.P. Rybkin, V.F. Shumeyko, and B.N. Topornin, 
chairman of the Public Chamber under the president, immediately 
set up a working group representing a wide range of public and 
social interests in order to stimulate the speediest adoption of 
amendments to tax legislation. 
  [signed] Vyacheslav Kostikov, Russian president's press 
secretary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

