<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Spokesman: Troop Unrest if Budget Not Increased </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Spokesman: Troop Unrest if Budget Not Increased </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505205294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1830 GMT 
25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Major General Vladimir Osadchiy, a key figure in the 
Main Military Budget and Financing Directorate of Russia's 
Defence Ministry, said that the social aspect has become 
decisive in the reform of Russia's armed forces. 
  Osadchiy believes that if the military budget is implemented 
in its present form then half of all servicemen will not be able 
to receive their pay within the term set by law. Two to three 
months without pay would lead inevitably lead to a worsening of 
the already difficult situation among the troops. 

</TEXT>

