<F P=106> [Aleksandr Veklich report: "Defense Sector on Its Knees"] </F>
  [Text] Novosibirsk -- Sixteen of the largest enterprises 
in Novosibirsk Oblast have closed down either partially or 
completely. While carefully fulfilling state orders and 
retaining the mobilization capacity required for them, the 
Novosibirsk defense sector has still not received payments of 41 
billion rubles due to it from the budget. 
  According to Anatoliy Yakovlev, chief of the Novosibirsk 
Oblast Administration's Machine Building and Defense Sectors of 
Industry Department, around 70 appeals have been sent to top 
organs of power. So far they have met with silence. Enterprise 
trade unions are planning a protest for 9 June. 

