<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bashkortostan Signs Power-Sharing Treaty With Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bashkortostan Signs Power-Sharing Treaty With Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505183794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1652 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 25 TASS -- Bashkortostan became on 
Wednesday the second republic after its neighbouring Tatarstan 
to sign a power-sharing treaty with Moscow. 
  The signing ceremony crowned a final round of negotiations 
between Russian Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin and Bashkir 
President Murtaza Rakhimov. 
  The package of signed documents includes agreements on 
economic cooperation, on foreign trade, on sharing powers in 
defence industries and state property ownership, on crime 
fighting and environment protection among others. 
  Drafted agreements on budget and banking relations remained 
unsigned as the parties failed to reach compromise in these 
fields. 

</TEXT>

