<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Late May Trip To Tatarstan Previewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Late May Trip To Tatarstan Previewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505194794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1905 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russian president's visit to Tatarstan scheduled 
for May 30-31 is a planned trip the head of state makes to 
various regions of Russia, Presidential Aide Anatoly 
Korabelschikov told Interfax. He pointed out that after Moscow 
and Kazan signed the Mutual Power Delegation Treaty, this visit 
had no political underlying. 
  According to Korabelschikov, the president will pay special 
attention to bringing on-line the motor plant damaged by a fire. 
The plant belongs to the association KamAZ, one of the biggest 
truck-manufacturing associations in Russia. During his visit, 
Yeltsin plans to examine principally new engines designed there, 
in particular the engines of new city buses. 
  The president is also interested in the creation of a 
financial and production group by KamAZ, Togliatti car-making 
plant and Avtovazbank. Such groups created in various regions 
of Russia are called to stimulate the development of 
top-priority branches of the economy, Korabelschikov said. 
  In Kazan, Yeltsin plans to meet with the Tatar leadership 
and 
visit a number of agricultural enterprises. 

</TEXT>

