<H3> <TI>   Parliamentarian Beaten; Leadership Accused of Suppression </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliamentarian Beaten; Leadership Accused of Suppression </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2505122094 Baku TURAN in English 1047 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2505122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (May 23) [date as received] TURAN--Today a 
member of Azerbaijan's Milli Majlis, Ibrahim Ibrahimli, was 
beaten after he exited the parliament building. According to 
Ibrahimli the police "asked him to come in to talk for about a 
minute." He refused to go with them, and they forcibly threw 
him into a car and took him to Baku's Chief Police Division. En 
route to the station, he was beaten. 
  According to witnesses, fifteen men took part in the 
beating. 
On May 21 Ibrahimli was severely beaten when a demonstration 
was dispersed and incurred serious injuries. According to 
unofficial sources, the leadership will continue to suppress the 
opposition. 

</TEXT>

