<F P=103> LD2505204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is the Georgian head of state's decree on the 
extension of the state of emergency in Abasha, Vani, Zugdidi, 
Lanchkhuti, Martvili, Mestia, Ozurgeti, Samtredia, Senaki, 
Khobi, Khoni, Tsalenjikha, Chokhatauri, and Chkhorotsku rayons 
and in the town of Poti: 
  With the aim of ensuring the security of citizens and 
consolidating law and order in all spheres of public and social 
life in West Georgia, and in accordance with the law of the 
Republic of Georgia of 6 November 1992 on state authority and 
the law of the Republic of Georgia of 11 December 1990 on state 
of emergency, the state of emergency in Abasha, Vani, Zugdidi, 
Lanchkhuti, Martvili, Mestia, Ozurgeti, Samtredia, Senaki, 
Khobi, Khoni, Tsalenjikha, Chokhatauri, and Chkhorotsku rayons 
and in the town of Poti is to be extended for two months from 23 
May 1994. 
  The parliament of the Republic of Georgia is requested to 
confirm the extension of emergency rules in West Georgia. 
  [signed] Eduard Shevardnadze. 

</TEXT>

