<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pro-Patria Proposes Parliament Speaker as Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pro-Patria Proposes Parliament Speaker as Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2505120894 Tallinn BNS in English 0924 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2505120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, May 25, BNS -- A general meeting of the 
Tallinn branch of Pro Patria yesterday decided to put forward 
parliament Chairman Ulo Nugis' name as new party chairman in 
preference over Prime Minister Mart Laar. 
  Most party members who spoke at the meeting criticized Laar 
and stated their support for Nugis. 
  The speakers voiced apprehension that, if Pro Patria 
continues under Laar's leadership, the party may not attain the 
5-percent threshold vote at the next parliamentary elections. 
  Nugis, too, was critical about the premier's performance and 
advised him to resign. 
  Pro Patria convenes in Tallinn June 11 to discuss election 
of 
new party chairman and the situation in the government and the 
ruling coalition. 
  The party council ruled on Monday [23 May] that election of 
new chairman doesn't automatically imply replacement of premier. 
Laar, on the other hand, asserted on Friday that he regards Pro 
Patria congress decisions as binding for himself. "If Pro Patria 
elects a new chairman I'll resign," he said. 

</TEXT>

