<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Minister Hits National Guard `Military Buildup' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Minister Hits National Guard `Military Buildup' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2505180394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 26 May 94 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM2505180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report under the general heading: "Crimea: Talks </F>
in Progress; No Easing of Tension"] 
  [Text] The formation of a 2,500 to 3,000-strong Ukrainian 
National Guard brigade is continuing in Crimea. This is what 
Major General Valeriy Kuznetsov, Republic of Crimea internal 
affairs minister, told an ITAR-TASS correspondent yesterday in 
an exclusive interview. 
  V. Kuznetsov pointed out that this military buildup is 
"unnecessary and atypical" of Crimea, which is already "awash 
with military formations and combat equipment." At the same 
time, he noted, Ukraine is indoctrinating and sounding out army 
units on the matter of the personnel's willingness to take 
practical action in the event of the introduction of a state of 
emergency in Crimea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

