<H3> <TI>   Tasks of Security Service in Crimea Outlined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tasks of Security Service in Crimea Outlined </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505153794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1228 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev, 25 May -- "Personnel of the Security Service's 
Main Directorate in Crimea are continuing to carry out their 
duties of protecting the security of the state in a precise and 
organized manner, in spite of the difficult political situation 
that has arisen around the regional branch of the special 
service." Thus, reads a release for the mass media circulated 
today by the press center of the Ukrainian Security Service. 
  The main task for staff of the Ukrainian Security Service's 
Main Directorate is vigorously to campaign against corruption 
and organized crime, to protect the region's economy from 
criminal violations, and to maintain peace and calm in the 
Republic of Crimea, the document stresses. Furthermore, the 
Security Service is closely collaborating with the internal 
affairs and procuracy bodies. The requirement to provide the 
president, the leaders of the parliament, and the Supreme Soviet 
of Crimea, and local authorities with full and objective 
information in the interests of resolving the autonomous 
republic's vital issues also remains in force. 

</TEXT>

