<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Warns Against Russian `Interference' in Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Warns Against Russian `Interference' in Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505123494 Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA in Ukrainian 24 May 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2505123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Undated "Statement by the Press Service of Ukraine's </F>
Ministry of Defense"] 
  [Text] The Russian mass media continue disseminating 
gossip [plitky] on the concentration of Ukrainian troops in the 
areas of Sevastopol and Simferopol. Open lies are carried with 
references to Minister of Defense of the Russian Federation 
Pavel Grachev and this, mildly speaking, gives rise to surprise. 
It only remains to wonder whether this is yet another political 
trick on the part of the Russian military ministry or its habit 
to rely upon dubious information sources. 
  Moreover, General Grachev makes statements whose content 
indicates that the Black Sea Fleet is commanded by the Defense 
Ministry of the Russian Federation. Besides, the fleet receives 
orders and directives from the Russian military department. 
Recently, Pavel Grachev ordered to decisively "counter all 
provocative actions with regard to the Black Sea Fleet 
facilities...." 
  The Press Service of Ukraine's Ministry of Defense is 
authorized to state that the interference by the Ministry of 
Defense of the Russian Federation into the affairs of the united 
Black Sea Fleet, which, in accordance with the Yalta accord, is 
directly subordinated to the presidents of Ukraine and Russia, 
impedes a civilized resolution of the problem of dividing the 
fleet and creates a dangerous tension in the Crimea. 

</TEXT>

