<H3> <TI>   Chernobyl AES Director Denies Possibility of `New Accident' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernobyl AES Director Denies Possibility of `New Accident' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605140194 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 25 May 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> AU2605140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "No Grounds for Panic"] </F>
  [Text] The distribution of iodine preparations to families 
in Chernihiv Oblast created panic among the population. In view 
of that, a news conference was held at which presidential 
representative in the oblast Valentyn Melnychuk stated that it 
had been a purely preventive measure, which had nothing to do 
with a "new" accident at the Chernobyl Atomic Electric Power 
Plant [AES]. Serhiy Parashyn, general director of the plant, 
assured journalists that his collective had "rendered such an 
accident impossible." In his opinion, the idea of closing down 
the Chernobyl AES has been artificially spread at the initiative 
of certain circles in the West. The people who are mainly 
interested in this are those trying to obtain funds from 
Ukraine's budget for implementing expensive projects. 

</TEXT>

