<H3> <TI>   Speaker Accused of Launching `Communist Coup' in Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaker Accused of Launching `Communist Coup' in Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505111094 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2145 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 24 May -- Opposition leader Vyacheslav 
Chornovil, said that what had taken place during a closed 
parliamentary session was a communist coup carried out under the 
leadership of Supreme Council Chairman Oleksandr Moroz. In his 
view, the election of deputy chairmen of the Supreme Council was 
carried out with numerous procedural violations, without 
announcing a continuation of plenary sittings of the Supreme 
Council, and the discussion of candidates lasted for only 30 
seconds. 
  As the leader of Rukh said during a conversation with a 
UNIAR 
correspondent, the Supreme Council Secretariat was not issuing 
copies of the verbatim record of the sitting to representatives 
of the Center group and the right-wing bloc. Chornovil believes 
that the possibility of falsifying the record exists. 
Representatives of four deputies' groups, Rukh, Center, Reform, 
and Statehood protested against the violation and said they were 
not prepared to take part in plenary sittings unless the 
election is declared invalid. Mr. Chornovil also said that 
obviously, deputies of the Center group and right of center 
groups would have to refuse to participate in forming the 
Cabinet of Ministers. 

</TEXT>

