<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK's Hurd on EU Ties, Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK's Hurd on EU Ties, Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505162494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1541 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vitaliy Makarchev] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 25 May TASS -- The implementation by Ukraine of 
the international agreement which obliges it to transfer its 
nuclear weapons to Russia is a separate issue and must not be 
connected with other problems, British Foreign Secretary Douglas 
Hurd said. 
  During his talks with Ukrainian top officials Hurd said that 
ten days ago EU [European Union] leaders discussed ways to 
expand ties between Brussels and Kiev and ensure control over of 
Ukraine's's part of the Soviet nuclear arsenal. 
  Despite attempts by some EU countries to interconnect these 
two issues, the European Council decided not to condition the 
signing of a comprehensive cooperation agreement with Ukraine on 
the full withdrawal of nuclear weapons from its territory, Hurd 
said. He also called Kiev to join as soon as possible the 
Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty. 
  Ukraine's participation in the treaty is very important not 
because the European Union is suspicious of Ukraine, but because 
it is much more concerned about the reaction to the current 
state of affairs from the countries seeking to obtain nuclear 
weapons, he said. 
  He said the EU believes the assurances received from 
Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk and his government that the 
agreement on the withdrawal of nuclear weapons will be strictly 
observed. He emphasised that neither Britain nor the European 
Union link the withdrawal of nuclear weapons with any of the 
existing problem. 
  Hurd called on the Ukrainian Parliament to give guarantees 
of 
the implementation of the agreement. Parliament Chairman 
Aleksandr Moroz assured Hurd that the lawmakers are strongly 
against nuclear weapons in Ukraine. 
  The British foreign secretary noted that there is only one 
way to solve the nuclear problem in Ukraine -- strictly observe 
and implement the agreement on the withdrawal of nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

