<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia To Have Use of Missile Attack Warning Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia To Have Use of Missile Attack Warning Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505165494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The latest round of Russo-Belarus negotiations on 
questions of military cooperation has been held in Minsk. As 
(?Venyamin Popov), the head of the Russian delegation stated, 
Russia will receive the possibility of using the radio station 
in Vileyka, even following the conclusion of the withdrawal of 
strategic forces from Belarus. Apart from that, construction of 
the missile attack warning radar station near Baranovichi will 
be completed. These facilities will also remain on Belarus 
territory even after the year 2000 and will operate in the 
interests of all member countries of the Treaty on Collective 
Security. 

</TEXT>

