<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Calls For Tougher Action Against Foreign Spies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Calls For Tougher Action Against Foreign Spies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605093094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0852 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 26 May (ITAR-TASS) -- President Boris 
Yeltsin called on Russian counterintelligence to intensify its 
counter measures against foreign special services which have 
stepped up their activities on Russian territory recently. 
  Speaking today at a conference of leaders of the Federal 
Counterintelligence Service [FSK], he set out the main 
objectives facing the FSK. ITAR-TASS has learned that, among 
other things, Boris Yeltsin called for greater efforts to 
forestall interethnic conflicts and a greater drive against 
organized crime, terrorism, and the drugs mafia. Success in 
these areas, the president believes, will help to boost the 
prestige and authority of counterintelligence agents in society. 
  The FSK, Boris Yeltsin stressed, must also safeguard the 
country's economic security. In order to meet these objectives 
the security organs must be strengthened, the president 
believes. Attestation carried out within the FSK has helped to 
increase their professionalism, he said. Boris Yeltsin 
expressed hope that counterintelligence agents will cope with 
the tasks they have been set. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

