<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk on Four Stages for Solution of Crimean Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk on Four Stages for Solution of Crimean Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505214094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2020 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [no dateline as received] On 25 May Ukraine's 
President Leonid Kravchuk visited the manuscripts department of 
the Taras Shevchenko Institute of Literature. During his 
meeting with employees of the institute he said it has become 
possible to split the solution of the Crimean issue into four 
stages: The first three envisage the division of the Black Sea 
Fleet, the determining of the sites for its bases, and the 
solution of the social and economic problems facing the 
peninsula. In the fourth and final stage, political 
arrangements should be worked out for settling all the problems 
around Crimea. "I always raise this question: Are we with 
Russia or under Russia?" Leonid Kravchuk asserted. 
  Touching on today's political situation in Ukraine, Leonid 
Kravchuk said that in political life, unfortunately, there is a 
repetition of something that occurred in 1990. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

