<H3> <TI>   Central Asian Science, Technology Council Meets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Asian Science, Technology Council Meets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605202294 Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network in Uzbek 0504 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network </F>
<F P=105>  Uzbek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The first sitting of the Consultative Council of 
the heads of state organizations for science and technology of 
the five Central Asian countries -- Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, 
Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, and Uzbekistan -- has been held in 
Tashkent. The new international organization was formed in line 
with the decision at the summit of the heads of states of the 
region. 
  The memorandum adopted in this connection outlines the basic 
areas for cooperation in the field of science and technology. 
The aim of the consultative council is to strengthen ties 
between the republics. The countries in the region will each 
formulate state science and technology rules. [passage omitted] 
  The scheduled sittings of the consultative council will be 
held in each of the five countries in turn. Many question on 
establishing useful and mutually beneficial cooperation still 
have to be examined. 

</TEXT>

