<H3> <TI>   Organization of `Unrecognized States' To Be Set Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Organization of `Unrecognized States' To Be Set Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2605120394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 26 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2605120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Sergey Bablumyan report: "Union of Unrecognized States </F>
Being Set Up?"] 
  [Text] Yerevan -- Robert Kocharyan, chairman of the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic State Defense Committee, has told 
journalists in Stepanakert that an organization uniting 
unrecognized states will soon be set up. 
  It is expected that it will include -- apart from the Crimea 
and the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic -- Abkhazia, Ajaria, South 
Ossetia, and the Dniester Republic. Robert Kocharyan expressed 
confidence that both the United Nations and the CSCE, as well as 
certain states, would have to take account of this newly created 
community. 

</TEXT>

