<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Admiral Cites Concrete Discussion on Fleet Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Admiral Cites Concrete Discussion on Fleet Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605123394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1152 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- Russian navy 
commander-in-chief Felix Gromov believes that the major 
achievement of the three-day Russian-Ukrainian talks in Moscow 
was that the sides switched from general declarations to a 
concrete discussion of the Black Sea Fleet share deal. 
  He told TASS on Thursday that "a basis had been laid for 
future goal-oriented work". 
  According to the admiral, during the ten-day break in the 
talks experts from both sides will specify the list of ships of 
the fleet, will study all its bases and assess the cost of the 
navy and shore facilities. 
  It has been agreed in principle that Ukraine will get 18 per 
cent of the fleet, according to Gromov. 
  He said that both the Russian and Ukrainian delegations came 
to the Moscow talks with their own plans of solving the dispute. 
However, a common variant was drafted on the first day and 
became the subject of all discussions. 
  The second round of talks is to be held in Kiev. 

</TEXT>

