<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "United States Worried by Rising Crime </F>
in Russian Federation"] 
  [Text] The unprecedented rise in organized crime in Russia 
poses a serious threat not only to its national security but 
also to the interests of Western countries, including the United 
States, according to participants in Wednesday's [25 May] 
hearings at the Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations of the 
U.S. Senate Committee for Governmental Affairs. 

