<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Colonel Andrey Bondarenko of the Volga Military </F>
District Press Center: "Cossacks Going to Dniester Region"] 
  [Text] Colonel General Georgiy Kondratyev, Russian deputy 
defense minister, has visited Totskiy garrison. He familiarized 
himself with the training of peacemaking troops of the 27th 
guards motorized infantry division to carry out missions in the 
Dniester region. 
  In the meantime, three transports carrying personnel, 
equipment, and arms of the motorized infantry regiment named for 
the Don Cossacks, set off for the Dniester Region to relieve the 
27th division subunits which are serving in the "trouble spot." 
  There are 97 direct descendants of the Don Cossacks from 
Rostov-na-Donu and Rostov Oblast serving in this unit. 

</TEXT>

