<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Will Not Dictate to Central, Eastern Europe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Will Not Dictate to Central, Eastern Europe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605123294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1137 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 26 May -- Russia not only wishes to, but 
will also remain a great power, stated Russian Defense Minister 
Pavel Grachev, replying to journalists' questions at a joint 
news conference with his Belgian counterpart Leo Delcroix, held 
in Brussels today. 
  The minister stressed furthermore that Russia does not 
intend 
to bring any pressure to bear on the countries of Central and 
Eastern Europe or to dictate its will to them. We favor equal 
and mutually beneficial cooperation with these states, he added. 

</TEXT>

