<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Meets With Balladur, Juppe in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Meets With Balladur, Juppe in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1235 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov, Andrey </F>
Krasnoshchekov, and Andrey Shtorkh] 
  [Text] Paris, 26 May (ITAR-TASS) -- During the interval 
between plenary sessions of the Conference on Stability in 
Europe a meeting was held at the initiative of France between 
French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur, French Foreign Minister 
Alain Juppe, and Andrey Kozyrev. Galina Sidorova, political 
adviser to the Russian foreign minister, told ITAR-TASS that the 
French leaders thanked the Russian minister for his agreement to 
take part in the conference and for Russia's active support for 
the idea of holding it. 
  The main subject of the conversation was ways of deepening 
relations between Russia and the principal European 
institutions. The Russian side believes that this process has 
not yet gathered sufficient momentum. The French leaders, for 
their part, called for the earliest possible conclusion of an 
agreement on partnership between Russia and the European Union 
[EU]. They stressed that Paris no longer sees any obstacles to 
completion of the negotiating process. All outstanding issues 
were settled during the recent official visit to Russia by A. 
Juppe. As we know, the main differences concerned conditions 
for trade in materials of the nuclear fuel cycle. 
  France considers that the conclusion of an agreement on 
partnership with the EU must be followed by further integration 
of Russia with other European organizations. 
  The entire atmosphere of the talks and the fact that the 
Russian minister was the only participant in the conference 
received by the French leaders so early in the conference 
testify to the present level of Russian-French cooperation, 
including cooperation in the preparation of this important forum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

