<H3> <TI>   State Duma Chairman Receives Iraqi Ambassador </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Chairman Receives Iraqi Ambassador </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605210594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1928 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By an ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- The majority of deputies of 
the State Duma, the lower house of the Russian parliament, 
believes that a sensible pragmatism should dominate in the 
Russian foreign policy, chairman of State Duma Ivan Rybkin said, 
receiving Iraqi ambassador in Russia Hasan Fahni Jum'ah on his 
request today. 
  "I want to tell you frankly that we would like to establish 
cordial and friendly relations between Russia and Iraq," the 
State Duma chairman said. He noted that with all changes taking 
place in Russia, the state leaders should not forget their old 
friends while making new friends. 
  Hasan Fahni Jum'ah, who has been performing his duties over 
the past five months only, emphasised Russia's influence at the 
international arena. "Taking into consideration a great 
potential of the Russian people, one can say that Russia will 
soon regain its past status in the world and restore the 
balance, which was completely destroyed during the recent 
years," the ambassador said. 
  Hasan Fahni Jum'ah and Ivan Rybkin also discussed the 
strengthening of bilateral, interparliamentary cooperation 
between Russia and Iraq, the State Duma press service informed 
ITAR-TASS. 

</TEXT>

