<H3> <TI>   Duma Votes Against No Confidence in Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Votes Against No Confidence in Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605122294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1123 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- The State Duma today voted 
against Sergey Baburin's move to express no confidence in the 
government. The move was put to the vote and turned down by the 
overwhelming majority of the deputies. 
  The attempt to topple the Chernomyrdin cabinet had been made 
hot on the heels of the debate in the lower chamber about the 
inadequate deliveries of food and petroleum products to Russia's 
northern regions this year. Baburin proceeded from the critical 
remarks made by the speakers who said the government was 
unjustifiably slow in organising the deliveries. 

</TEXT>

