<F P=106> [Report by Captain 2nd Rank Vladimir Gundarov in the "News </F>
From the Regions -- From Our Correspondents" column: 
"Perestroyka on the Border"] 
  [Text] Murmansk -- Protection of Russia's state border in 
the arctic region will be restructured taking into account the 
development of links with Norway and Finland and also the 
opening of the Northern sea route to foreign vessels with calls 
at Russian ports. This requires the creation of a Northern 
Border District whose area of responsibility will stretch from 
the Kola Peninsula to Chukotka. This was announced by Colonel 
Anatoliy Koretskiy, chief of the Murmansk border guard 
operations department. 

