<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no dateline as received] -- Today, as the 
country holding the European Union [EU] Presidency, the Greek 
embassy in Ukraine issued a statement on events in Crimea. The 
document reads: "The European Union expresses grave concern at 
the developments in Ukraine's Crimean region and backs further 
efforts on the settlement of the problems on the basis of law by 
