<H3> <TI>   Swiss Delegation Discusses Missile Technologies Control </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Swiss Delegation Discusses Missile Technologies Control </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2705090394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0800 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2705090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Swiss delegation, headed by Rolf (Hessler), 
deputy secretary for foreign economic issues, envoy of the 
Federal Council for Control Over Exports, is visiting Ukraine at 
the invitation of the Ukrainian Foreign Ministry. The 
delegation was received by First Deputy Foreign Minister Mykola 
(Mytarenko). The guests held a number of meetings, in 
particular with Volodymyr Horbulin, general manager of the 
National Technical Agency. The sides discussed the issues 
concerning Ukraine's future access to the system of control over 
missile technologies [SCMT]. The system currently includes 25 
states, whose governments have agreed to adhere to jointly 
adopted principles and regulations while international transfer 
of [word indistinct] equipment and technologies, in order to 
prevent the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction 
delivery systems. Mr. (Hessler), currently the SCMT head, highly 
assessed the steps taken by the Ukrainian Government to 
establish efficient control over the exports of appropriate 
products and technologies. 

</TEXT>

