<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportedly Preparing for Presidential Rule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605151194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1125 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Ukraine and Crimea have pledged to resolve the 
dispute about the degree of autonomy enjoyed by the Crimean 
peninsula through negotiations. However, according to the 
statement of Ukraine's deputy prime minister Zhulynskyy, 
President Kravchuk intends to dissolve the Crimean Parliament in 
the near future and introduce presidential rule on the territory 
of the peninsula in the event of the Crimean legislators 
refusing to reject the new constitution. It is still not clear 
what place Crimean President Meshkov occupies in the political 
plans of President Kravchuk. One thing is clear -- at any 
moment the situation may get out of control. 

</TEXT>

