<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Asserts That Peace Guarantees Exist in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meshkov Asserts That Peace Guarantees Exist in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605150394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1342 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Sergey Karmalito] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol, 26 May (ITAR-TASS) -- "Guarantees of 
stability and peace in Crimea exist and they will be provided 
for," Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov said today at a session of 
the Crimean parliament which took place here. "There are no 
fears, no threats, `the hot heads' are surrounded by normal, 
calm people and they will not be permitted to work their evil 
deeds either in Crimea or Ukraine, or anywhere else," he 
stressed. 
  The president of Crimea appealed to representatives of the 
mass media to reassure their listeners, viewers, and readers. 

</TEXT>

