<H3> <TI>   Crimean Security Chief Says Kravchuk Decree Illegal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Security Chief Says Kravchuk Decree Illegal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605203094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1600 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, [no dateline as received] -- A statement 
by Volodymyr Lephykhov, the chairman of the Security Service of 
Crimea, was circulated in the republic today. 
  Volodymyr Lephykhov believes that the decree by the 
president 
of Ukraine "On the Main Directorate of the Security Service of 
Ukraine in Crimea," signed on 18 May, violates the law of 
Ukraine "On the Security Service." The Supreme Council of 
Ukraine did not consider the changes connected with the decree 
by Leonid Kravchuk, and there is no resolution by the Supreme 
Council of Ukraine that would legally fix the changes in the law. 
  In the opinion of Volodymyr Lephykhov, all this gives 
grounds 
to believe that the decree by the president of Ukraine of 18 May 
"is illegal and illegitimate in all respects." 
  "In the present-day complicated situation such actions raise 
strong doubts about the assurances by the official circles of 
Ukraine that they wish to ensure durable civil peace and accord, 
the rights and freedoms of every citizen in Crimea," says the 
statement by the Crimean Security Service chairman. 

</TEXT>

