<H3> <TI>   Supreme Council Appoints Heads of Commissions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supreme Council Appoints Heads of Commissions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605204594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1758 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian Supreme Soviet Speaker Aleksandr Moroz 
told deputies today that Communist representatives would head 
the parliamentary commission on the fuel and energy complex, 
that on transport and communications and the commission on 
legislation and law. 
  Moroz said that a RUKh [Ukrainian People's Movement for 
Perestroyka] representative would lead the commission on nuclear 
policy and nuclear safety. 
  The Unity faction will lead the commission on juridical 
policy and state structure, that on local government and the 
commission on economic policy. 
  Representatives of the Center group will head the commission 
on health care, protection of childhood and motherhood and that 
on basic industries and social-economic development of regions. 
  Moroz commented on the balance of forces in the parliament. 
It is the following: the communist faction - 87 
representatives; the Center deputy group - 43; the socialist 
faction - 25; the agrarian faction - 33; the Unity faction - 
27; the Reforms deputy group - 26 and the Statehood faction 26 
representatives. There are 41 independent deputies who have 
joined none of these groups or factions. 

</TEXT>

