<F P=103> LD2605212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev May 27 TASS -- President Leonid Kravchuk of 
Ukraine met with a delegation of the General Agreement on 
Tariffs and Trade (GATT), led by Andy Stoler, chairman of 
commission on Ukraine's joining the GATT, on Thursday. 
  The visitors are taking part in the governmental conference 
on Ukraine's joining GATT and the World Trade Organisation in 
Kiev. 
  The process of Ukraine's joining GATT has already begun, 
Kravchuk told the delegation. 
  It is rather important for our economy and development of 
the 
country on the whole. We are aware that the process of entering 
GATT has its laws and regulations and will do our utmost to pass 
it as soon as possible, Kravchuk said. 

