<H3> <TI>   Army Official Reports No Draft Dodging </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Official Reports No Draft Dodging </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605130094 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0720 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 26 May -- "There is no disruption in the 
staffing of troop units today," said Major-General Valeriy 
Venher, head of the main organization and mobilization 
directorate of the general Headquarters of Ukraine's Armed 
Forces, at an armed forces briefing on the problems of staffing 
and conscription. 
  With regard to the "Crimean problem", Valeriy Venher said 
that conscription in Crimea is going according to plan, and that 
the military commissar in the autonomy is obeying only the 
orders of Ukraine's commander in chief and minister of defense. 
  Valeriy Venher refused to quote any figures concerning the 
draft or discharge, saying "they are not to be made public." 
He did say that 800 people did alternative service last year. 
On the whole, the head of the organization and mobilization 
main directorate believes, this type of service found little 
support among conscripts. 

</TEXT>

