<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sabotage Act Against Sevastopol Military Unit Foiled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sabotage Act Against Sevastopol Military Unit Foiled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605214394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605214394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Defense Ministry press service issued 
a report in which it draws attention to the instances connected 
with a provocation attempt against the command post of the radio 
engineering brigade of the anti-aircraft defense forces of our 
state located in Sevastopol. Two instances have occurred over 
the past few days that testify to such intentions. What the 
press service has in mind is the fact that places, prepared by 
unknown persons for planting an explosive, and a wire laid down 
to blow it up, were discovered near the above command post. 
Quite probably, says the report, this could have been done by 
an unknown person detained here, who turned out to be a reserve 
Black Sea Fleet officer. A large amount of the explosive has 
been confiscated from him. 
  The Ukrainian Defense Ministry press service reports that 
competent bodies launched an investigation into the above 
instances. The name of the detained person has not been 
disclosed so far in the interests of the investigation. 

</TEXT>

