<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Addresses Counterintelligence Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Addresses Counterintelligence Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Argues `Efficient' Special Services Needed </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605152294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1339 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Yeltsin stated that Russia needed reliable 
and efficient special services. "We must shake off the burden 
of totalitarianism, but do away with the destructive moods in 
the Federal Counterintelligence Service [FSC]," he told the 
FCS's national conference on Thursday. 
  To quote Yeltsin, Russia must play a worthy role in the 
world 
community and efficiently protect its independence, territorial 
integrity and historical traditions. 
  He also said that new approaches must be laid to the system 
of Russian security. "We must have a systematic and exhaustive 
information about the situation in Russia and around it," he 
said. Yeltsin expects the Federal Counterintelligence Service to 
provide clear-cut estimates and ideas on ways of neutralizing 
and eliminating threats to Russia's security. He also said that 
the FCS must give forecasts and proposals on possible political 
decisions. The FCS has a sufficient potential for analysis and 
operational forecasts, said Yeltsin. 

</TEXT>

