<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Better Rapport Between Branches of Power Urged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Better Rapport Between Branches of Power Urged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605123794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1040 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- A working group consisting of 
representatives of the president, members of the government and 
Russian lawmakers suggested a single concept of adopting laws 
aimed at the formation of civic society in Russia. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS presidential aide Georgiy 
Satarov pointed out that laws on elections, referendums, parties 
and local government "should be adopted in a single package 
which would meet comprehensive principles of interaction between 
society and the state." 
  For the realisation of the proposal members of the working 
group expressed support to the initiative suggested by the 
Russian president, the Federation Council and the State Duma to 
set up a joint commission for coordinating legislative 
activities of the branches of power. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

