<H3> <TI>   Liberal Union Deputy Assaults Zhirinovskiy Aide </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liberal Union Deputy Assaults Zhirinovskiy Aide </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2605104094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 26 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2605104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX-NG report: "Gentlemen's Quarrel"] </F>
  [Text] State Duma Deputy Andrey Makarov (from the "12 
December" Liberal Democratic Union faction) assaulted Captain 
Second Rank Mikhail Ivanov, adviser to Liberal Democratic Party 
of Russia [LDPR] chief Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, on Wednesday. The 
victim said that he was trying to hand over the seventh and 
eighth chapters of the global concept of public security in 
Russia he had drawn up to Yuliy Gusman, his colleague in the 
deputy corps. In response to Gusman's flat refusal to 
familiarize himself with the paper, Captain Ivanov himself 
acknowledged, he said imprudently: "If you don't read it you 
will end up like Makarov." Hearing his name is so dubious a 
context, Andrey Makarov hit the LDPR adviser with a case, 
smashed his lip, tore off a pocket from his uniform, and tried 
to tear his shoulder boards. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

