<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Blasted for Refusing To Publish Protest Letter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Blasted for Refusing To Publish Protest Letter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605154694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1046 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Council of the Liberal-Democratic Party 
[LDP] accused the editor-in-chief of the newspaper Izvestiya of 
refusing to publish its letter of protest against Yegor Gaydar's 
article entitled "A Stalk on Rascals." The article said that 
"all the classical attributes of a fascist party, ideology and 
personality perfectly apply to Zhirinovskiy and his party." 
  The Liberal Democratic Party's appeal to Izvestiya, handed 
to 
Interfax, says that instead of initiating a direct dialogue 
between political opponents, Izvestiya was playing into the 
hands of politicians of the same bias, publishing articles 
discrediting the Liberal Democratic Party one after another. 
  The letter says that the Liberal Democratic Party leaders, 
"considered their duty to inform its electors of their attitude 
to Gaydar's dirty article through any other Russian newspaper 
which will not be afraid to give space to the party which won 
the election on December 12, 1993." 

</TEXT>

