<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gerashchenko Denies Opposing Edicts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gerashchenko Denies Opposing Edicts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605151394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1424 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 26 BUSINESS-TASS -- Chairman of the 
Russian Central Bank Viktor Gerashchenko refuted mass media 
reports that he opposed the package of economic decrees recently 
issued by President Boris Yeltsin. 
  Gerashchenko told BUSINESS-TASS that those documents had 
actually been prepared by specialists from the Central Bank, 
along with other departments. They were then only polished up 
by the president's staff. 
  "The aim of the published decrees is to raise contract 
discipline and achieve the honoring of responsibilities before 
each other and before the state", the chairman noted, adding 
that the decrees would be fully implemented by the Central Bank. 
  The only thing that might have given rise to the rumours of 
his opposition, said Gerashchenko, was his comment, made at a 
recent meeting of the government, that the system of final 
editing of decrees and documents could be improved. He said the 
government should avoid changing documents which have already 
been fully prepared, since that might lead to some 
misunderstandings. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-64087 </DOCNO>
