<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bank Plans Hidden Currency Interventions by Proxy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bank Plans Hidden Currency Interventions by Proxy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2705093194 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 27 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2705093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Federation Central Bank </F>
Changes Tactics of Currency Market Regulation"] 
  [Text] The Russian Central Bank plans to change its 
tactics of regulating the ruble's exchange rate against the 
dollar by carrying out hidden interventions through networks of 
authorized banks. At the same time, the Central Bank is going 
to reduce its presence at the Moscow Interbank Currency 
Exchange, Igor Knyazev, deputy chief of the bank's currency 
operations administration, said. This scheme is expected to be 
more efficient because authorized banks will benefit from 
putting their into circulation, which, in turn, will create a 
"cash flow." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

