<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Authorities Deny Accusations of Arms Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Authorities Deny Accusations of Arms Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605162894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1238 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] May 26 TASS--Leaders of the 
Dniestr [Dniester] region regarded as slander the statements 
made by commander of the 14th Russian Army Aleksandr Lebed who 
accused Tiraspol leaders of illegal possession of weapons and 
asked the Russian leadership to deprive them of Russian 
citizenship which they were abusing. 
  According to Vladimir Ivanov, aid to the president of the 
Dniestr Republic, Tiraspol leaders really have firearms in 
personal possession but he stressed that these weapons were 
handed to them in a legal way. He also confirmed that some 
Dniestr leaders were granted Russian citizenship but denied the 
statements of the command of the 14th Army accusing them of 
abusing this citizenship for illegal trade in weapons. 
  A spokesman for the Interior Ministry of Moldavia [Moldova] 
told ITAR-TASS that the police also had information about 
misappropriation, illegal possession and re-sale of weapons by 
Tiraspol leaders and mafioso structures in the Dniestr Republic 
patronized by them. 

</TEXT>

