<H3> <TI>   Dniester Asks Russia To Ship Banknotes to Tiraspol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Asks Russia To Ship Banknotes to Tiraspol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705075094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1900 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2705075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 25/5/1994 -- The government of 
the self-proclaimed Dniester republic today requested President 
Boris Yeltsin and the Federal Assembly to facilitate the 
shipment of Dniester rubles to Tiraspol. Boris Akulov, deputy 
of the Dniester supreme soviet, told BASA that the banknotes are 
currently stored at the Gosznak plant in Moscow. Previously, 
some Russian organs blocked their shipment to Tiraspol. This 
decision was later annulled by the Russian Arbitration Court at 
the Dniester official's request. According to Akulov, there is 
the shipment of banknotes to Tiraspol. A delegation comprising 
Dniester deputies and public organization representatives has 
been organized and will leave tomorrow for Moscow to conduct 
negotiations on shipping the banknotes as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

