<F P=103> NC2605114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 26 May (SNARK)--Armenian Internal Affairs 
Minister Vano Siradegyan, appearing by a TV, called criminal the 
Trade Minister Tigran Grigoryan. "The May 10 arrest of trade 
minister, while he took a 2,500-dollar bribe, was carried out 
smartly", told Siradegyan. 
  As already reported, two days after his detention the trade 
minister was released, because no prosecutor sanction was 
submitted during his arrest. He took up his office again. 
  From a TV screen, Vano Siradegyan announced: "All officials 
with whom I have talked accepted that trade minister is a thief 
and bribe-taker, however they required proof, being doubtful 
about the sum as low as 2,500 dollars. But it's a teacher's 
salary for 50 years", exclaimed Siradegyan. He promised to 
arrest next time the state minister red handed--instead of a 
minister--and present the proper videotape. 

</TEXT>

