<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Abkhazians Killed in Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Abkhazians Killed in Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605202494 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1430 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- For the past two days 
Abkhaz separatists have been conducting intense artillery 
shelling of the environs of the village of Ajara, along with 
carrying out provocative sorties against Georgian people's 
voluntary corps, thus violating the Moscow cease-fire agreement. 
Gudauta militants carry out armed raids on peaceful villages of 
the area, later accusing the Georgian side in order to gain over 
public opinion. 
  Yesterday [25 May], Abkhazian mercenaries units attempted to 
attack Georgian positions. Georgian Armed Forces units and the 
local population, who until then had refrained from any 
retaliatory actions, had to open fire. The opposite side 
retreated suffering casualties. Six attackers were killed and 
two taken prisoner. 
  Embittered by this failure, Abkhaz separatists dropped four 
bombs on the village of Ajara yesterday at one p.m.; luckily, 
there were no casualties. 

</TEXT>

