<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazian Deputy Demands Shevardnadze's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazian Deputy Demands Shevardnadze's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605194594 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1400 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 26th [dateline as received] -- Boris 
Kakubava, an MP and chairman of the Abkhazian Liberation Union, 
has made a speech at a rally held by opposition parties in front 
of the Tbilisi Cinema House today. He said that the 
parliamentary minority fails to oppose a policy conducted by the 
Georgian head of state. He referred to the parliamentary 
majority as a society of deaf- mutes. 
  In Boris Kakubava's opinion, Georgia will not be able to get 
back its lost territories while Eduard Shevardnadze is the head 
of state. He has demanded that Eduard Shevardnadze resign 
voluntarily. 
  According to Boris Kakubava, the Union of Georgia's Citizens 
is trying to mislead and deceive the Georgian people. The 
Georgian authorities have used 26 May, Georgia's Independence 
Day, to demonstrate the strength of Russian troops in Georgia. 
  In Boris Kakubava's words: "We will not allow anyone to 
overthrow the present authorities by force. If we are together, 
we will survive. If we stay apart, we will be destroyed one by 
one." 

</TEXT>

