<F P=102>   LD2705103894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0848 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Peking, 27 May -- A meeting between Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, Chairman of the Russian Federation Government, who 
is on an official visit to China, and Jiang Zemin, Chairman of 
the PRC, took place today in the state residence of Zhongnanhai. 
  "I believe that cooperation between the two countries is 
developing very successfully", Jiang Zemin said, opening the 
meeting. He expressed confidence that the visit of the head of 
the Russian Government would give a new boost to economic 
cooperation. 
  Viktor Chernomyrdin conveyed to PRC Chairman Jiang Zemin 
greetings from Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin and 
his invitation to visit Russia in early September this year. 
  During the course of the meeting Viktor Chernomyrdin also 
pointed out that Russo-Chinese relations are flourishing and are 
not dependent on changes in the political scene. The level of 
mutual relations and cooperation which has been achieved between 
Russia and China gives hopes for Rusian-Chinese relations to be 
switched to a higher stage -- a stage of economic cooperation. 

</TEXT>

