<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, May 27 (TASS) -- An agreement on the regime 
of the Russo-Chinese state border was signed here on Friday by 
Viktor Chernomyrdin, the prime minister of the Russian 
Federation, and Li Peng, premier of China's Council of State, at 
the close of Russo- Chinese talks held by the official 
delegations of the two countries. 
  The two sides also signed another six intergovernmental 
documents: an agreement on the prevention of double taxation 
and income tax evasion, a protocol of the second session of the 
Russo- Chinese intergovernmental commission on technical, 
economic, scientific and technical cooperation, agreements on 
economic, scientific and technical cooperation in the 
agro-industrial centre, on cooperation in sea shipping, 
environmental protection, and on protection, regulation and 
reproduction of the living resources in the border sections of 
the Amur and Ussuri rivers. 

