<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in N. Ossetian Emergency Zone `Sharpens' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in N. Ossetian Emergency Zone `Sharpens' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605174494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1353 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz May 26 TASS -- The situation in the zone 
under state of emergency on the territory of North Ossetia has 
sharpened again, according to military sources. 
  This is connected with the fact that on May 25 at about 9 
p.m. unidentified persons shot at a Zhiguliy car with two people 
inside near the village of Yuznyy situated in the security zone. 
Both people died of mortal gunshot wounds. The incident is 
being investigated. 
  The situation in the zone under state of emergency is 
aggravated by acts of terrorism, bandit attacks and incessant 
taking of hostages, a spokesman for the press service of the 
president and the government of North Ossetia told ITAR-TASS. 
  Unfortunately, so far the fate of three citizens of North 
Ossetia taken hostages in the village of Maiskiy of the 
Prigorodnyy district on March 30 this year, is not known yet. 
  The measures carried out to search and liberate six Ingushes 
who were taken hostages by criminals on May 19 in the city of 
Vladikavkaz have not produced positive results either. 
  Today President of North Ossetia Akhsarbek Galazov met with 
members of the presidiums of the government and the parliament 
of the republic, representatives of the law enforcement bodies 
of North Ossetia and the temporary administration. They 
discussed urgent measures to search for the hostages. 
  The president expressed an extremely negative attitude to 
the 
unlawful actions of persons involved in the crimes in the 
Maiskiy village and in Vladikavkaz, and stated that the 
leadership of North Ossetia would do everything in its power to 
find hostages and take additional measures to ensure security of 
residents of the republic. 

</TEXT>

