<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Proposes Topics for CIS September Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Proposes Topics for CIS September Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005100694 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Commonwealth of Independent States should 
become a genuine economic union of the former USSR republics, 
said CIS Executive Secretary Ivan Korotchenya, who was on a 
visit to Almaty, speaking to journalists after his talks 28 May 
with President Nazarbayev. [passage omitted] 
  According to the executive secretary, the summit will be 
preceded by a meeting of foreign and defense ministers who will 
have to agree on a number of important documents to be signed by 
the heads of the republics. 
  Ivan Korotchenya also said that during his talks with 
President Nazarbayev, the president put forward a number of 
interesting proposals aimed at further strengthening ties 
between the republics. These ideas will be made public shortly 
and are likely to prevail during the forthcoming September 
summit. 
  The executive secretary focused special attention on a 
message from President Yeltsin of Russia to the heads of the CIS 
states stressing the need for joint peace-making efforts in 
Georgia. 
  According to Ivan Korotchenya, the Kazakh leader supported 
Yeltsin. Korotchenya will also have talks in Bishkek, Dushanbe, 
and other CIS capitals. 

</TEXT>

