<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Makes Budget Recommendations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Makes Budget Recommendations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705220694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1222 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705220694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 27 May -- When the State Duma looks at the 
second reading of the draft 1994 budget on 8 June, the Budget, 
Taxes, Banks, and Finance Committee will recommend that the 
deputies cut spending on a range of articles in the document 
being debated. Committee Deputy Chairman Gennadiy Kulik informed 
correspondents about this today at a news conference. Among 
other things, he said the committee is in favor of cutting 
outlay on foreign economic activities by 2 trillion rubles and 
cutting spending on the state management apparatus by 550-560 
billion rubles. 
  Gennadiy Kulik stressed that the committee will recommend 
that Duma deputies increase defense spending by 3.5-4 trillion 
rubles, and essential scientific research by 700 billion rubles. 
  Kulik also said that in the draft 1994 budget it is planned 
to allocate in all 15.3 trillion rubles to the agro-industrial 
complex. Out of this sum, 5.6 trillion rubles is to be spent on 
purchasing food at federal and regional level. 
  Gennadiy Kulik also stressed that the committee will advise 
the Duma to allocate 1 trillion rubles toward the creation of a 
special leasing fund to sell machinery to agricultural producers 
in installments. 

</TEXT>

