<H3> <TI>   Law on Publishing Constitutional Laws Adopted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Law on Publishing Constitutional Laws Adopted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM3005091594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 27 May 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM3005091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Federal Law `On the Procedure </F>
for the Publication and Enactment of Federal Constitutional 
Laws, Federal Laws, and Acts of Chambers of the Federal 
Assembly' Was Adopted 25 May by the State Duma"] 
  [Text] As we know, on 25 May the Duma had already adopted 
this law, but it had not been approved by the Federation 
Council. In this connection, a coordination commission was 
created, made up of representatives of both chambers of the 
Federal Assembly and the Russian Federation president. It 
prepared a new single text of the law. 
  The adopted document envisages that the day of the adoption 
of a federal law by the State Duma in its final wording is 
considered to be the date of its adoption. The date of the 
adoption of a federal constitutional law is the day when it is 
approved by the Federal Assembly chambers according to the 
procedure established by the Russian Federation Constitution. 
  According to the document, the first publication of a 
federal 
constitutional law, a federal law, or an act of a Federal 
Assembly chamber in its full text in ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA or 
SOBRANIYE ZAKONODATELSTVA RF is considered to be the official 
publication. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

