<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Budget Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Discusses Budget Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005161994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An expanded session of the Cabinet of Ministers 
chaired by Prime Minister Sergey Tereshchenko was held on 30 May 
with the participation of the heads of republican departments 
and deputy heads of oblast administrations and the 
administrations of Almaty and Leninsk. 
  After listening to a report by Finance Minister Yerkeshbay 
Derbisov, the session examined the updated state budget for 
1994. Since the beginning of this year, as is known, the 
republic has lived according to the budget endorsed in January 
by the decree of the president of Kazakhstan in the absence of 
the legislature. This period in the life of society, linked 
with a deepened economic crisis, has objectively led to a new 
spiral of inflation, and additional measures are now needed to 
curb the inflation. 
  The draft updated budget which will be submitted to the 
Supreme Kenges of the new convocation is characterized by a 
strict financial concept. The budget envisages a deficit not 
higher than 4 percent. This corresponds to the norms of the 
international financial banking organizations. 
  During the discussion on the budget, proposals were voiced 
to 
support the basic industries, the development of entrepreneurial 
structures, acceleration of market reform, and also to increase 
social protection for low-income groups. 
  Vice President Yerik Asanbayev and Supreme Kenges Deputy 
Chairman Marat Ospanov took part in the session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

