<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe May 30 TASS -- Executive Secretary of the 
Commonwealth of Independent States Ivan Korotchnya has conducted 
a three-day visit to the Tajik capital of Dushanbe to discuss 
the expansion of economic, political and military cooperation 
between the CIS countries and to examine the situation on the 
border between Tajikistan and Afghanistan. 
  Korotchnya met with Tajikistan leader Emomali Rakhmonov, 
Prime Minister Abduzhalil Samadov, and other officials of the 
republic. 
  Tajik Parliamentary Chairman Rakhmalov and Korotchnya 
visited 
the 12th post of the Moscow border guard on Sunday. There they 
laid a wreath of flowers at the obelisk erected in memory of the 
22 Russian border guards who were killed in an unequal battle 
with Tajik opposition forces and mujahideen fighters from 
Afghanistan on July 12, 1993. 
  The CIS executive secretary departed for Moscow Monday 
morning. 

</TEXT>

