<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Official Explains Purpose of Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Official Explains Purpose of Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705165394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0900 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 27 May -- "The purpose of my visit to 
Tajikistan is to have talks with the republican leadership on 
further steps by the UN with regard to participating in finding 
a settlement to the inter-Tajik conflict," Marrack Goulding, UN 
under secretary general for political questions, told a group of 
Russian correspondents on arrival in Dushanbe. The second round 
of inter- Tajik talks, he said, is due to take place in Tehran 
on 7 June. 
  Asked by a correspondent if the question on enhancing the 
status of the Dushanbe official delegation at the talks would be 
raised during the meetings, Marrack Goulding stressed that he 
would not like to go into details at this moment. He promised 
to speak in detail about the results of his meetings with the 
Tajik leadership, including his meeting with Emomali Rahmonov, 
at a news conference. 
  Marrack Goulding reaffirmed that he is bringing with him a 
note from UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali for Emomali 
Rahmonov, chairman of the Tajik Supreme Soviet. However, he 
said, he would not wish to reveal the contents of this note just 
now. 
  A meeting will take place today between Marrack Goulding and 
Tajik Foreign Minister Rashid Alimov, Labor and Employment 
Minister Shukur Zukhurov, and Security Minister Said Amir 
Zukhurov. During his visit the UN under secretary general will 
be received by Tajik Premier Abdulmadjid Samadov. 

</TEXT>

