<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Agreements Signed With Malaysia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation Agreements Signed With Malaysia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005204494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1809 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Singapore, 30 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Turkmenistan and 
Malaysia have today signed five agreements on trade and economic 
cooperation, scientific and technical cooperation, visa 
arrangements for travel, and mutual debt payment. 
Turkmenistan's President Saparmurad Niyazov, who is paying an 
official visit to Kuala Lumpur, and the Malaysian Prime minister 
Mahathir bin Mohamad, were present at the signing ceremony. 
  According to an official spokesman of the Malaysian Foreign 
Ministry, Mahathir bin Mohamad promised his Turkmen guest to 
share experience in the sphere of privatizing state-owned 
enterprises and implementing economic reforms. Turkmenistani 
nationals will study banking in Malaysia. The visitors also 
said they would be interested to learn from Malaysians how to 
set up free economic zones. 
  Giving a speech today at the National Chamber of Trade and 
Commerce, Niyazov called upon the Malaysians to step up their 
investment in the branches of industry that are actively 
developing in Turkmenistan, such as the oil and gas industry, 
tourism, and others. 

</TEXT>

