<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Rules Out Official Relations With Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Rules Out Official Relations With Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005172994 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1500 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Estonia, 30 May -- The Ukrainian Embassy in 
Estonia has received a note from the Estonian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs. The document says that in accordance with the 
treaty on friendship and cooperation between Ukraine and 
Estonia, which reaffirms the two countries' territorial 
integrity and inviolability of their borders, Estonia will be 
guided by these principles in its policy toward Crimea and 
considers establishment of any official relations between 
Tallinn and Simferopol impossible. 

</TEXT>

