<H3> <TI>   Declaration To Begin Free Trade Talks With Slovenia Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Declaration To Begin Free Trade Talks With Slovenia Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS3105085694 Tallinn ETA in English 0701 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3105085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From 30 May RAHVA HAAL, p.1; "News Bulletin" No. 106/94 ] </F>
  [Text] Estonian Prime Minister Mart Laar and Slovenian 
Prime Minister Janez Drnovshek signed a declaration to begin 
free trade negotiations. Estonia has already started such talks 
with Poland, Hungary and Czech Republic. According to Laar 
Slovenia may become a "gate to former Yugoslavia, also to 
Italy". Laar remarked on the similarity of security problems in 
Estonia and Slovenia and mentions the possibility of defence 
cooperation. Estonia has appointed Sven Jurgenson for its 
charge d'affaires in Slovenia. 
  Slovenian Prime Minister had a positive attitude to 
Estonia's 
suggestion to enact visa-free travel. 

</TEXT>

