|products    |            |            |ls, oil     |            |            | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Non-preciou-|10.9        |(13.6)      |Vehicles    |10.8        |(10.0)      | 
|s metals    |            |            |            |            |            | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Clothes     |8.4         |(11.5)      |Mechanical  |10.1        |(10.0)      | 
|            |            |            |devices     |            |            | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Vehicles    |7.9         |(9.4)       |Electrical  |7.8         |(8.9)       | 
|            |            |            |devices     |            |            | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  The report by the Customs Department reflects the goods and 
commodities declared on the border. The report doesn't include 
data about the movement of cash and of commodities transported 
through pipelines. The figures include imports for and exports 
following duty-free storaging of goods in Estonia. 

</TEXT>

