<H3> <TI>   President Notes `Preventive Diplomacy' in Russian Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Notes `Preventive Diplomacy' in Russian Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005175194 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 30 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ulmanis said today that the principle of 
preventive diplomacy is a characteristic feature of the process 
of concluding Latvian-Russian agreements on army withdrawal. 
His remarks came at a news conference covering Ulmanis's recent 
trip to the United States. He emphasized that the principle of 
preventive diplomacy has now been put forward at the UN as the 
corner stone of activity, because with its help it is possible 
to tackle many issues in the world. 
  UN Secretary-General Butrus Ghali, meeting with Ulmanis, 
promised to render UN assistance in the process of setting up 
the Baltic peacekeeping battalion by providing specialist 
training. 
  Ulmanis noted that protection of individual rights rather 
than states rights is currently being given more emphasis at the 
UN at this time. 

</TEXT>

