<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bundestag Increases Coal Subsidy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundestag Increases Coal Subsidy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904105994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0954 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The Bundestag today approved an 
increase in the coal subsidy over the votes of the opposition. 
This means the surcharge on electricity bills to subsidize the 
German coal industry will increase in 1995 from 7.5 to 8.5 
percent. The subsidy is to be introduced in eastern Germany in 
1996 at a rate of around 4.25 percent. The new arrangement is 
necessary because the Century Agreement, which governs the use 
of German coal for electricity supplies, runs out at the end of 
next year. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

