<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   BND Officials Charged With Attempted Arms Export </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BND Officials Charged With Attempted Arms Export </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804192594 Munich ARD Television Network in German 1800 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich ARD Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Charges have been brought against two high-ranking 
officials of the Federal Intelligence Service [BND]. The State 
Prosecutor's Office in Hamburg today confirmed a report on the 
ARD news magazine "Panorama," which will be broadcast after this 
news bulletin. 
  The charge is violation of the law controlling the export of 
war weapons. The two allegedly attempted in 1991 to ship two 
antiaircraft tanks of the NVA [former GDR's National People's 
Army] to Israel declaring them as agricultural machinery. 

</TEXT>

