<F P=106> ["grd"-signed report: "`Close Down All Nuclear Power </F>
Plants'"] 
  [Excerpt] Hamburg -- Lower Saxony, Schleswig-Holstein, and 
Hamburg want to renounce nuclear power. This was agreed at a 
meeting in Hamburg by minister-presidents Gerhard Schroeder, 
Heide Simonis, and Mayor Henning Voscherau (all Social 
Democratic Party). The three laender are planning to coordinate 
their future energy policies within the "regional development 
concept." This will include closing down all nuclear power 
plants, Schroeder said. 
  The three heads of government have, however, not yet agreed 
on a date for opting out of nuclear power. "We do not want to 
pressure ourselves," Schroeder said. Specific steps can be 
expected next year. There will be talks with the major power 
suppliers in northern Germany over the next few months, where 
economically feasible alternatives to nuclear power will be 
discussed. Voscherau and Schroeder did not say which 
alternatives they have in mind. Ms Simonis indicated, however, 
that a more intense use of coal would be the obvious choice. 
She urged the other laender to close down their nuclear power 
plants as well. "Quitting nuclear power can only be successful, 
if all laender join in." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

