<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Arrives for Talks With Daimler-Benz </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Arrives for Talks With Daimler-Benz </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205091394 Hamburg DPA in German 0824 GMT 2 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0205091394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stuttgart -- PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat has arrived 
in Stuttgart this morning. This was announced by the press 
office of the airport. The chairman of the PLO Executive 
Committee is honoring an invitation by Daimler-Benz chief Edzard 
Reuter. During his one-day visit to the Swabian capital, 
'Arafat, who is being accompanied by a delegation of close 
economic and political advisers, will meet with Reuter and the 
board of directors of the concern. In addition, the company 
plans a product and research presentation for the Arab host. 
  Baden-Wuerttemberg's Minister President Erwin Teufel 
(Christian Democratic Union) will receive 'Arafat for an 
exchange of views on the peace process in the Middle East. 
Subsequently, Teufel will host a dinner for his visitor. 

</TEXT>

