<H3> <TI>   Agrees on `Intensive Cooperation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agrees on `Intensive Cooperation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205105494 Hamburg DPA in German 1026 GMT 2 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0205105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stuttgart (DPA) -- Daimler-Benz Chief Edzard Reuter 
and PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat have agreed on more intensive 
cooperation, above all in border-crossing infrastructure 
projects. This was announced by Reuter, who had invited 'Arafat 
for a one-day visit to Stuttgart, in a talk with journalists on 
Monday [2 May]. "We at Daimler-Beinz are convinced that the 
peace process in the Middle East can be consolidated through the 
contribution of European companies," Reuter said. The meeting 
with 'Arafat is a good starting point for the accelerated 
expansion of economic cooperation. 
  Reuter promised his guest that a development study would be 
drawn up to solve the infrastructure and traffic problems in 
Palestine as a gift. The study will compiled by the 
corporation's subsidiary Donier Management Consulting. 'Arafat, 
who said that economic recovery is one of the most important 
bases for the pace process in the Middle East, accepted the gift 
with thanks. 'Arafat came to Stuttgart two days before the 
planned signing of the Gaza-Jericho autonomy agreement. 

</TEXT>

