<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi `Optimistic' About Forming Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi `Optimistic' About Forming Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2904111094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1054 GMT 29 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2904111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Government, Berlusconi `Fairly </F>
Optimistic'"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, April 29 -- Prime Minister-designate 
Silvio Berlusconi, leaving his Roman residence this morning, 
told reporters he was "fairly optimistic" he could form a 
government in reasonable time. 
  His morning's agenda included meetings with Northern League 
representatives Umberto Bossi and Roberto Maroni, with life 
Senator Paolo Emilio Taviani, and with Rome Mayor Francesco 
Rutelli. 
  Asked about the controversy over the sensitive post of the 
Interior Ministry, the Forza Italia leader said that "We still 
have to go into all that but I don't see any insurmountable 
problems." 
  His Northern League allies have pressed to obtain that post, 
but other political forces have vetoed that, saying the League 
could open up a Pandora's box if they got their hands on 
sensitive police and security roles and files. 
  The list of potential ministers was "still up in the air," 
he 
said. 
  Formal consultations on the cabinet are slated to begin 
Monday [2 May]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

