<F P=106> [Report by Anabel Diez and Luis R. Aizpeolea: "PSOE </F>
Leadership Insists Solchaga Does Not Have To Resign Yet"] 
  [Excerpt] Madrid - The scandals surrounding Mariano Rubio 
and Luis Roldan will not at the moment lead to resignations in 
the PSOE [Spanish Socialist Workers Party]. At the current 
state of the investigation, the party leadership does not 
consider there to be any political liability attached to former 
ministers Carlos Solchaga and Jose Luis Corcuera, during whose 
terms the irregularities were committed. This prevailing view 
in the Socialist executive was revealed at Monday's [25 April] 
meeting and confirmed in the course of the week. However, 
Secretary General Felipe Gonzalez has yet to make a statement: 
Everyone hopes he will do so today at the Federal Committee 
meeting convened to approve the electoral lists. [passage 
omitted] 

