<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia's Silajdzic: UN `Must Act, Carry Out Strikes' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnia's Silajdzic: UN `Must Act, Carry Out Strikes' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205095694 Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG in German 1 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> AU0205095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Bosnian Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic: "Air </F>
Strikes -- United Nations Must Act"] 
  [Text] Europe also becomes guilty of the genocide in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina because it allows the Belgrade government to 
pursue its plan of a greater Serbian empire unimpeded. 
  We call on the community of peoples to make it unmistakably 
clear to the Belgrade regime that it cannot keep the towns and 
villages that it conquered with brute force, and that the state 
borders must not be changed. The United Nations must no longer 
act as a neutral mediator, it must act and carry out air strikes 
against those who violate the UN resolutions. The Belgrade 
government must know that it can no longer attack UN protected 
areas unpunished and fetch its heavy weapons from UN depots at 
will to continue the genocide somewhere else -- in Brcko 
probably. 
  I appeal to Chancellor Kohl to help us. Aggression must not 
be rewarded. It must not be allowed that somebody who attacks a 
home and kills the people living there can keep the house as a 
reward. We call on the international community to convene a 
large world peace conference. 
  Those who do not help in Bosnia-Herzegovina are putting a 
fuse to a powder keg that may set Europe aflame. We want our 
civilization to survive where laws and moral principles should 
prevail and not murder and violence. 

</TEXT>

