<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Arrives in Stuttgart for 1-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Arrives in Stuttgart for 1-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205091294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0821 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0205091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stuttgart (DDP/ADN) -- PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat 
has arrived for a one-day visit to Stuttgart. This morning he 
will meet the leadership of the Daimler-Benz group, and a 
meeting between 'Arafat and chief executive Edzard Reuter is 
also planned. According to Daimler-Benz AG, 'Arafat's visit is 
"an important element in the group's strategy of actively 
supporting the peace process in the entire Middle East region." 
  The PLO chairman is accompanied by his closest economic and 
political advisors. During his visit to Daimler-Benz, 'Arafat 
will be shown products and research projects. The talks will 
focus on extending telecommunication systems and solving 
transport problems in the Middle East. 
  This evening 'Arafat is to meet Baden-Wuerttemberg's Prime 
Minister Erwin Teufel. The ministry of state announced that 
their talks will focus on the Middle East peace process and the 
role of the PLO. Afterward, Teufel will host a reception and 
dinner in honor of his guest at the Neues Schloss [New Palace] 
in Stuttgart. 

</TEXT>

