<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "No Trust in Assurances"] </F>
  [Excerpt] During their visit to Bavaria and talks with 
representatives of the CSU [Christian-Social Union], the SPD 
[Social Democratic Party of Germany], the FDP [Free Democratic 
Party], and the Greens, representatives of the Turkish DEP 
[Democratic Party], the only pro-Kurdish party in the Turkish 
parliament, warned against sending Kurds back to Turkey. Under 
no circumstances must the German authorities trust the 
assurances of the Turkish authorities, said DEP deputy Ali Yigit. 
  "Hundreds of people have disappeared while in police 
custody. 
Every Kurd sent back from here will meet a similar fate," said 
Yigid, who also met the mayor of Munich, Christian Ude. 
[passage omitted] 

