  [Text] Munich (DDP/ADN) -- The Bundeswehr may soon be 
flying over 200 MiG-29 fighters. The news magazine FOCUS 
reports that a Kremlin offer to this effect was put to the 
German Finance Ministry two weeks ago and was being examined. 
At present, 24 such aircraft were deployed from stocks of the 
GDR People's Army. 
  Manfred Opel, the SPD [Social Democratic Party] defense 
expert, said the purchasing price totalled 4 billion marks. He 
said the amount could be deducted from the debts owed to Bonn by 
Moscow. 

