<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Waigel Urges Greater `Returns' From EU Money </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Waigel Urges Greater `Returns' From EU Money </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004160394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1438 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Wuerzburg (ddp/ADN) -- "Returns" from the European 
Union (EU) to Germany must be "improved", according to Theo 
Waigel, chairman of the Christian Social Union [CSU] and finance 
minister. At a CSU meeting in preparation for the European 
elections, Waigel said today in Wuerzburg that Germany has 
fallen from position two to position seven in the EU prosperity 
league after unification. The call for an austere budget policy 
in Europe and increased returns for Germany is therefore 
justifiable. 
  Waigel once again called for an international Bundeswehr 
commitment within the United Nations. Germany has to be 
prepared to assume responsibility "in Europe and throughout the 
world. We cannot hide any longer," Waigel stressed. 

</TEXT>

